<body>

  <main>

    <h1>Privacy Policy for Shahi Pharma</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 25, 2026</p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Welcome to Shahi Pharma. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use,
        disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our mobile
        application and website (the "Service"). Shahi Pharma is a B2B order
        management platform.
      </p>
      <p>
        Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you do not agree with the
        terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the application.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect information that you voluntarily provide to us when you
        register on the app, express an interest in obtaining information about
        us or our products, or otherwise contact us.
      </p>

      <h3>Personal Data</h3>
      <p>
        Information such as your name, business name, email address, phone
        number, and delivery address that you provide during account
        registration and order placement.
      </p>

      <h3>Order Information</h3>
      <p>
        Details regarding the medicines and products you request or order
        through our B2B platform.
      </p>

      <h3>Cookies and Tracking</h3>
      <p>
        We use cookies (such as language preference cookies) and similar
        tracking technologies (like JWT authentication tokens) to keep you
        logged in and remember your settings.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect or receive to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Facilitate account creation and the login process.</li>
        <li>Fulfill and manage your orders, requests, and payments.</li>
        <li>Send administrative information such as updates to our terms, conditions, and policies.</li>
        <li>Improve app functionality and user experience.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We may share your data with third-party vendors, service providers,
        contractors, or agents who perform services for us or on our behalf.
        These include:
      </p>

      <h3>Cloud Hosting & Storage</h3>
      <p>
        We use secure cloud services (such as Render and Cloudinary) to host our
        application and store uploaded images or documents.
      </p>

      <h3>Database Management</h3>
      <p>
        We use secure database services (like MongoDB) to store your account and
        order information.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Security of Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures
        (including secure HTTPS connections and encrypted passwords) to help
        protect your personal information. However, no electronic transmission
        over the internet or information storage technology can be guaranteed
        to be 100% secure.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
      <p>
        We will only keep your personal information for as long as it is
        necessary for the purposes set out in this privacy policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may request to review, update, or delete the personal information
        we have collected from you by contacting us using the information
        provided below.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions or comments about this Privacy Policy or wish to
        request the deletion of your account data, please contact us at:
      </p>

      <p><strong>Email:</strong> [Insert Your Support Email]</p>
      <p><strong>Phone:</strong> [Insert Your Business Phone Number]</p>
    </section>

